<div class="wrapper-content">
  <div class="full-up formatting">
    <h2>Lifelong Learners</h2>
    <p>Whenever curiosity is piqued, so to is an enthusiasm to learn. The key trait of a lifelong learner is curiosity. Cultivating this trait begins with questions that evoke further thinking. Most questions begin and end with fact. What is the sum of this? Who invented that? Deep questioning challenges students to understand context and prompts them to consider <em>why</em>. Verso trains teachers to ask deep questions by providing an instant feedback loop to immediately measure and respond to how their students understand activities.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="collage">
  <div class="grid-1 bg-image-texture-inclass"></div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper-content">
  <div class="full-up formatting">
    <h2>Inverted Learning</h2>
    <p>Verso builds upon the flipped classroom learning model which inverts traditional teaching methods. Instruction is delivered through the app outside of class while ‘homework’ is done inside the classroom. Concept mastery therefore happens in class with the guidance of peers and teachers.</p>
    <p>Impacting learning necessitates an inclusive product development strategy. Since it’s impossible to foretell the devices accessible to schools and families, we used the same robust web codebase to launch the Verso experience on all major platforms and devices. Doing so reduced the total scope of the engineering while accelerating time to market.</p>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="collage">
  <div class="grid-1 bg-image-devices"></div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper-content">
  <div class="full-up formatting">
    <h2>Boundless Classrooms</h2>

    <p>Humans never stop learning, so why are there constraints on the time and place students learn? We had to divorce the idea of a classroom from physical space in order to move it to the digital realm. A digital classroom is boundless, it persists wherever there are curious people and is only a push notification away.</p>

    <p>A digital classroom must mirror the buzz of its physical counterpart. We imbued this sense of activity by surfacing student feedback the instant it happened. The adoption of student anonymity created a peer-pressure free social dynamic where students could express themselves without fear of being judged. We created feedback mechanisms like ‘helpfuls’ and ‘grouping’ to help identify the strongest student responses to be used as future discussion points. Combined, the features created to a vibrant communication system that showcased meritorious ideas while also activating the voice of even the meekest students.</p>
  </div>
</div>

